cff-version: 1.2.0
title: DFO Benchmark Suite
message: >-
  If you use this benchmark suite in academic work, please cite both
  the suite (this entry) and the accompanying paper (preferred-citation).
type: software
authors:
  - family-names: Madeira
    given-names: José F. Aguilar
    email: aguilarmadeira@tecnico.ulisboa.pt
    affiliation: >-
      IDMEC, Instituto Superior Técnico, Universidade de Lisboa;
      ISEL, Instituto Politécnico de Lisboa
    orcid: 'https://orcid.org/0000-0001-9523-3808'
repository-code: 'https://github.com/aguilarmadeira/DFO_Benchmark_Suite'
abstract: >-
  Benchmark suite for derivative-free optimization, organized by
  decision-variable type. The current release provides 63 bound-constrained
  test problems with continuous variables and 504 self-contained MATLAB
  wrappers (63 problems × 8 scaling strategies) for evaluating algorithmic
  robustness under heterogeneous variable scales, together with a
  standalone scaling toolkit applicable to user-supplied problems.
keywords:
  - derivative-free optimization
  - benchmarking
  - scale heterogeneity
  - scale invariance
  - global optimization
  - direct search
  - engineering design
license: LGPL-3.0-or-later
